Lagos – Gbenga Ashafa, Senator representing Lagos East Senatorial District, in partnership with Rotary Club Palm Groove and Indo Eye Hospital, has organised a free medical surgery for 160 constituents of Lagos East Senatorial District. Ashafa media team said, “This partnership is in line with the Senator’s commitment to provide complete sequence of treatment for all those diagnosed of different eye diseases at the Lagos East Senatorial District town hall meeting/free medical outreach of December 21, 2017. The surgery to be performed on the beneficiaries involves Pterigum excision and Cataract extraction. “The beneficiaries include constituents across every age bracket and gender, including a three-year-old child who would benefit from this programme as well. “The medial outreach which commenced on Monday, February 25, 2018 will come to an end on Friday, March 2, 2018 when the last batch of beneficiaries were operated upon. On Saturday, March 3, 2018 the Senator joined his partners and the beneficiaries at an event which commemorated the opening of the eyes of the beneficiaries operated upon. This event took place at the Lagos Island General Hospital. Ashafa at the event expressed his appreciation to all who had made the free eye surgery a success particularly the sponsors of the event and called on all Nigerians to always contribute their quota to healthcare development and provision of health care to the indigent in the society. 1 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.